Package view

This package contains the classes that define the views of the application.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    About
    This class defines the view that shows the information of development group of the application.
    BuoyData
    This class defines the view to enter, show or modify the information of a buoy.
    DatasetFileConverter
    This class defines the view to convert an intermediate or pre-processed dataset file into CSV or ARFF format.
    Index
    This class defines the main view of the application.
    LoadMatchingFile
    This class defines the view to load or delete the information stored in a XML file and related to a matching process.
    ManageBuoys
    This class defines the view to manage the information of the buoys entered in the application.
    ManageReanalysisData
    This class defines the view to manage the information of the reanalysis data files entered in the application.
    NewDatasetFile
    This class defines the view to create a new intermediate dataset file.
    NewMatchingFile
    This class defines the view to create a new XML file with the information related to a matching process.
    NewPreprocessedDatasetFile
    This class defines the view to create a new pre-processed dataset file.
    OpenARFFfile
    This class defines the view to open an ARFF file with WEKA tool.
    OpenDatasetFile
    This class defines the view to open an intermediate or pre-processed dataset file for being pre-processed.
    RunCreationDataset
    This class defines the view to start the process of creation of an intermediate dataset file.
    RunMatching
    This class defines the view to start the process of creation of the final datasets.
    SelectBuoyAttributes
    This class defines the view to select the attributes of the buoy to use in the matching process.
    SelectReanalysisFiles
    This class defines the view to select the reanalysis data files to use in the matching process.

Package view Description

This package contains the classes that define the views of the application.
